<item>
            <title>[LU-8657] Wireshark dissectors for Lustre fail to build against Wireshark 2.2.0 source.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8657</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Starting with version 1.99.2 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Commit: 7ced085&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; , Wireshark has completely eliminated the &quot;emem&quot; API and has replaced it with the new &quot;wmem&quot; API. The dissector code for Lustre still references the old API which fails to build against more recent Wireshark source code. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Wireshark 2.2.0</environment>
        <key id="40222">LU-8657</key>
